<item>
            <title>[GROOVY-4923] Creating Pattern from declared String variable  with pattern = ~stringvariable fails</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/GROOVY-4923</link>
                <project id="12318123" key="GROOVY">Groovy</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;An attempt to create a java.util.regex.Pattern from a variable that is declared as a String fails with a java.lang.ClassCastException: java.util.regex.Pattern cannot be cast to java.lang.String&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The code below worked with Groovy 1.7.8 but fails with Groovy 1.8.0&lt;br/&gt;
String value=&quot;test&quot;&lt;br/&gt;
String s = &quot;^\\S+$value\$&quot;&lt;br/&gt;
def p = ~s &amp;lt;==Fails here&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;A workaround is to change the last statement to:&lt;br/&gt;
def p = ~/$s/&lt;br/&gt;
but that adds clutter&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment>Windows 7 64bit, 32 bit jvm 1.6.0_26</environment>
